<B>
	IND
</B>
	&#148; means (i)&nbsp;an investigational new drug application filed with the FDA, and its equivalent in other countries or regulatory jurisdictions, for authorization to commence clinical studies and (ii)&nbsp;all supplements and amendments that may be filed with respect to the foregoing.
</P>

</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Indication
</B>
	&#148; means a primary sickness or medical condition or any interruption, cessation or disorder of a particular bodily function, system or organ (each a &#147;disease&#148;) requiring a separate Phase 3 Clinical Trial to obtain Regulatory Approval to market and sell a product for such disease, and shall include sub-types of the same disease and pediatric populations of the same disease (i.e., such sub-types and pediatric populations shall be part of the Indication and shall not be treated as separate Indications).
</P>

</B>
	&#148; means all technical, scientific and other know-how and information, trade secrets, knowledge, technology, means, methods, processes, practices, formulae, instructions, skills, techniques, procedures, experiences, ideas, technical assistance, designs, drawings, assembly procedures, computer programs, apparatuses, specifications, data, results and other material, including: biological, chemical, pharmacological, toxicological, pharmaceutical, physical and analytical, pre-clinical, clinical, safety, manufacturing and quality control data and information, including study designs and protocols, assays and biological methodology, in each case (whether or not confidential, proprietary, patented or patentable) in written, electronic or any other form now known or hereafter developed.
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(i)&nbsp;not generally known and (ii)&nbsp;necessary or reasonably useful for the Exploitation of the Licensed Compound or a Licensed Product or any Improvement thereto, but excluding any Information to the extent covered or claimed by published Insmed Patents or Joint Patents or any Joint Know-How.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>

	1.75.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Insmed Patents
</B>
	&#148; means all of the Patents Controlled by Insmed or any of its Affiliates or its or their Sublicensees as of the Effective Date or that are made or conceived by Insmed or any of its Affiliates or its or their Sublicensees at any time during the Term that are necessary or reasonably useful (or, with respect to Patent applications, would be necessary or reasonably useful if such Patent applications were to issue as Patents) for the Exploitation of the Licensed Compound or a Licensed Product or any Improvement thereto, but excluding any Joint Patents.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</FONT>

	1.76.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">

</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Insmed Regulatory Documentation
</B>
	&#148; means all Regulatory Documentation Controlled by Insmed or any of its Affiliates directly relating to the Licensed Compound or a Licensed Product in the Field in the Territory.

</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	that portion of the annual fee on prescription drug manufacturers imposed by the U.S. Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act, Pub. L. No.&nbsp;111-148 (as amended) that Insmed, its Affiliate or its or their Sublicensees, as applicable, allocates to sales of the Licensed Products in accordance with Insmed&#146;s, its Affiliates&#146; or its or their Sublicensees&#146; standard policies and procedures consistently applied across its products, as applicable; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1.93.9.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	any other similar and customary deductions that are consistent with GAAP.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Any of the deductions listed above that involves a payment by Insmed, its Affiliates or its or their Sublicensees shall be taken as a deduction in the Calendar Quarter in which the payment is accrued by such entity.&#160; For purposes of determining Net Sales, a Licensed Product shall be deemed to be sold when invoiced and a &#147;sale&#148; shall not include transfers or dispositions of such Licensed Product for pre-clinical or clinical purposes or as samples, in each case, without charge.&#160; Insmed&#146;s, its Affiliates&#146; or its or their Sublicensees&#146; transfer of any Licensed Product to an Affiliate or Sublicensee shall not result in any Net Sales, unless such Licensed Product is consumed or administered by such Affiliate or Sublicensee in the course of its commercial activities.&#160; With respect to any Licensed Product that is consumed or administered by Insmed or its Affiliates or its or their Sublicensees, Net Sales shall include any amount billed or invoiced with respect to such consumption or administration, including any services provided in connection therewith.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In the event that a Licensed Product is sold in any country in the form of a Combination Product, Net Sales of such Combination Product shall be adjusted by multiplying actual Net Sales of such Combination Product in such country calculated pursuant to the foregoing definition of &#147;Net Sales&#148; by the fraction A/(A+B), where A is the average invoice price in such country of any Licensed Product that contains the same Licensed Compound(s)&nbsp;as such Combination Product as its sole active ingredient(s), if sold separately in such country, and B is the average invoice price in such country of each product that contains active ingredient(s)&nbsp;other than the Licensed Compound(s)&nbsp;contained in such Combination Product as its sole active ingredient(s), if sold separately in such country;
<I>
	provided
</I>
	that the invoice price in a country for each Licensed Product that contains only the Licensed Compound(s)&nbsp;and each product that contains solely active ingredient(s)&nbsp;other than the Licensed Compound(s)&nbsp;included in the Combination Product shall be for a quantity comparable to that used in such Combination Product and of substantially the same class, purity and potency.&#160; If either such Licensed Product that contains the Licensed
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	Compound(s)&nbsp;as its sole active ingredient or a product that contains an active ingredient (other than the Licensed Product) in the Combination Product as its sole active ingredient(s)&nbsp;is not sold separately in a particular country, the Parties shall negotiate in good faith a reasonable adjustment to Net Sales in such country that takes into account the medical contribution to the Combination Product of and all other factors reasonably relevant to the relative value of, the Licensed Compound(s), on the one hand and all of the other active ingredient(s), collectively, on the other hand.

	that any such allocation to a Licensed Product shall be (i)&nbsp;done in accordance with Applicable Law, including any price reporting laws, rules&nbsp;and regulations, and (ii)&nbsp;subject to clause (i), in no event no greater than a pro rata allocation, such that the portion of each of the foregoing rebates, discounts and other forms of reimbursements shall not be included as deductions from Invoiced Sales hereunder in any amount greater than the proportion of the undiscounted Dollar value of such Licensed Product sold by Insmed, its Affiliates or its or their Sublicensees to Third Parties hereunder compared to the undiscounted Dollar value of all the products sold by Insmed, such Affiliates and such Sublicensees to Third Parties to which such foregoing rebate, discount or other form of reimbursement, as applicable, are granted.

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1.109.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Regulatory Documentation
</B>
	&#148; means:&#160; all (i)&nbsp;applications (including all INDs and Drug Approval Applications), registrations, licenses, authorizations and approvals (including Regulatory Approvals); (ii)&nbsp;correspondence and reports submitted to or received from Regulatory Authorities (including minutes and official contact reports relating to any communications with any Regulatory Authority) and all supporting documents with respect thereto, including all adverse event files and complaint files; and (iii)&nbsp;clinical and non-clinical and other data contained or relied upon in any of the foregoing; in each case ((i), (ii)&nbsp;and (iii)) relating to the Licensed Compound or a Licensed Product or any Improvement thereto.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1.110.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	Regulatory Exclusivity Period
</B>
	&#148; means, with respect to each Licensed Product in any country in the Territory, any period of data, market or other regulatory exclusivity (other than Patent exclusivity) granted or afforded by Applicable Law or by a Regulatory Authority in such country that confers exclusive marketing rights with respect to such Licensed Product in such country or prevents another party from using or otherwise relying on any data supporting the approval of the Drug Approval Application for such Licensed Product without the prior written consent of the holder of the Regulatory Approval.&#160; Such data, market or other regulatory exclusivity may include new chemical entity exclusivity, new use or indication exclusivity, new formulation exclusivity, orphan drug exclusivity, non-patent related pediatric exclusivity or any other applicable marketing or data exclusivity, including any such periods listed in the Orange Book or any such periods under national implementations in the EU of Article&nbsp;10 of Directive 2001/83/ED, Article&nbsp;14(11) of Parliament and Council Regulation (EC) No.&nbsp;726/2004, Parliament and Council Regulation (ED) No.&nbsp;141/2000 on orphan medicines, Parliament and Council Regulation (ED) No.&nbsp;1901/2006 on medicinal products for pediatric use and all international equivalents of any of the foregoing.
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1.112.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	&#147;Residual Knowledge&#148;
</B>
	means any ideas, concepts, know-how and techniques generally relating to the treatment, diagnosis, cure, mitigation or prevention of any Indication within the Field which are not specifically related to the Licensed Product or the Licensed Compound, and that are contained in or derived from Confidential Information that is acquired and retained solely in, and Insmed first reduces to tangible form solely from, the unaided memories of Insmed or its Affiliates or its or their Sublicensees who have had access to AstraZeneca&#146;s Confidential Information under this Agreement.&#160; An individual&#146;s unaided memory will be considered to be unaided if the individual has not intentionally memorized the Confidential Information for the purpose of retaining and subsequently using or disclosing it.

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1.133.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	&#147;Valid Claim
</B>
	&#148; means (i)&nbsp;a composition of matter or method of use claim of any issued and unexpired Patent whose validity, enforceability or patentability has not been affected by (a)&nbsp;irretrievable lapse, abandonment, revocation, dedication to the public or disclaimer or (b)&nbsp;a holding, finding or decision of invalidity, unenforceability or non-patentability by a court, governmental agency, national or regional patent office or other appropriate body that has competent jurisdiction, such holding, finding or decision being final and unappealable or unappealed within the time allowed for appeal or (ii)&nbsp;a composition of matter or method of use claim of a pending Patent application that was filed and is being prosecuted in good faith and has not been abandoned or finally disallowed without the possibility of appeal or re-filing of the application;
<I>
	provided
</I>
	that such prosecution has not been ongoing for more than [***].
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	1.134.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	&#147;
<B>
	VAT
</B>
	&#148; has the meaning set forth in Section&nbsp;7.8.2.

	Subject to Sections&nbsp;2.3, 2.4, 2.5, 5.4 and the other terms and conditions of this Agreement, AstraZeneca hereby grants to Insmed:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

	an exclusive license (or sublicense), with the right to grant sublicenses in accordance with Section&nbsp;2.3, under the AstraZeneca Patents, the AstraZeneca Know-How and AstraZeneca&#146;s interests in the Joint Patents and the Joint Know-How, to Exploit the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products and any Improvements thereto in the Field in the Territory;
<I>
	provided, however
</I>
	, that Insmed may, at any time during the Term and in its sole discretion, opt out of licensing any AstraZeneca Patent or AstraZeneca&#146;s interest in a Joint Patent, in which case, upon written notice from Insmed to AstraZeneca, such Patent will automatically be excluded from this license grant and shall no longer be treated as an AstraZeneca Patent or Joint Patent (as applicable) for any purpose under this Agreement; and

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	2.5.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	AstraZeneca&#146;s Right of First Negotiation.
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	2.5.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Before Insmed or any of its Affiliates commences any confidential discussions with any Third Party pursuant to a confidential disclosure agreement regarding a transaction to sell, assign, license, sublicense or otherwise dispose of Insmed&#146;s right to Develop or Commercialize any Licensed Product in the Field in any part of the Territory to any Third Party to permit such Third Party to Develop or Commercialize such Licensed Product in the Field in such part of the Territory, or if Insmed receives an unsolicited offer for such a transaction, then prior to negotiating with or entertaining further offers from any Third Party to acquire such right,&nbsp;Insmed first shall notify AstraZeneca of its intent or receipt of offer (as applicable), and provide to AstraZeneca a copy of any additional data with respect to the Development and Commercialization of the Licensed Products in the Field not previously provided to AstraZeneca.&#160; AstraZeneca shall have [***], or, in the case of Insmed&#146;s receipt of an unsolicited offer, [***], after receipt of such notification and additional data (the &#147;
<B>
	ROFN Period
</B>
	&#148;) to elect to enter into exclusive negotiations for the right to Develop or Commercialize such Licensed Product in the applicable part of the Territory.&#160; During the ROFN Period,&nbsp;Insmed
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	and its Affiliates shall not negotiate with or grant any rights to Develop or Commercialize Licensed Products to any Third Party.&#160; If AstraZeneca elects to enter into exclusive negotiations during the ROFN Period,&nbsp;Insmed shall negotiate exclusively and in good faith with AstraZeneca for a period commencing upon the date Insmed receives notice of such election from AstraZeneca and expiring [***] thereafter (the &#147;
<B>
	Negotiation Period
</B>
	&#148;) with respect to commercially reasonable terms for the acquisition by AstraZeneca, by license or otherwise, of the right to Develop or Commercialize the Licensed Product in the Field in such part of the Territory.&#160; Notwithstanding the foregoing in this Section&nbsp;2.5.1, each Party shall retain all discretion to determine, among other things, whether any proposed terms for AstraZeneca&#146;s right to Develop or Commercialize any Licensed Product in the Field in any part of the Territory during the Negotiation Period are acceptable to such Party, and no Party shall be deemed to have acted without good faith solely because such Party does not agree to some or all of the other Party&#146;s proposed terms, or if the Parties cannot come to an agreement on mutually acceptable terms within the Negotiation Period.&#160; For the avoidance of doubt, (i)&nbsp;nothing in this Section&nbsp;2.5.1 shall limit Insmed&#146;s right to sublicense any rights in whole or in part to any Affiliate, Third Party contract research organizations and/or Third Party contract manufacturing organizations, as set forth in Section&nbsp;2.3, or to engage a Third Party Distributor to the extent reasonably necessary or useful for the Commercialization of Licensed Products in the Territory, and (ii)&nbsp;no Change of Control of Insmed or its Affiliates or Sublicensees shall trigger AstraZeneca&#146;s rights under this Section&nbsp;2.5.1.

</B>
	&#160; During the period beginning on the Effective Date and continuing until [***], AstraZeneca shall not conduct a research program, either alone or in collaboration with any Third Party, the primary goal of which is to Develop or Commercialize any DPP1 Compound, except for any Licensed Compound being Developed or Commercialized by AstraZeneca pursuant to the terms of this Agreement or another agreement between Insmed and AstraZeneca or any of their respective Affiliates.

<B>
	Insmed&#146;s Right of Negotiation for AstraZeneca Respiratory IMED Bronchiectasis Compounds.
</B>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	2.7.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	During the period beginning on the Effective Date and continuing until [***], if AstraZeneca&#146;s Innovative Medicines and Early Development unit with responsibility for respiratory pharmaceutical products (the &#147;
<B>
	Respiratory IMED
</B>
	&#148;) develops a compound with a molecular weight of [***] and plans for the primary Indication to be Bronchiectasis, AstraZeneca shall notify Insmed.&#160; For clarity, such notice requirement shall be triggered if such compound is determined by the Respiratory IMED to be a &#147;
<B>
	Candidate Drug
</B>
	,&#148; meaning it is eligible for initiation of a Phase 1 Clinical Trial, and the written plan for development in connection with such compound&#146;s designation as a &#147;Candidate Drug&#148; is for the first Phase 2 Clinical Trial to be for patients with an Indication of Bronchiectasis.&#160; If the Respiratory IMED&#146;s initial written plan for development of such compound is for the first Phase 2 Clinical Trial to be for patients with an Indication other than Bronchiectasis, such notice requirement shall not be triggered upon the designation of the compound as a Candidate Drug,
<I>
	provided
</I>
	that if development of the compound thereafter ceases for all Indications except that it is ongoing or planned for Bronchiectasis, then such notice requirement shall be triggered on the basis that Bronchiectasis has become the primary Indication for such compound.&#160; A notice provided under this Section&nbsp;2.7.1 shall be a &#147;
<B>
	Bronch CD Notice
</B>
	&#148; and the compound referred to therein shall be a &#147;
<B>
	Bronch CD
</B>
	.&#148;

<B>
	Bronch CD Notice Period
</B>
	&#148;) to elect to enter into exclusive negotiations for the right to develop or commercialize such Bronch CD.&#160; During the Bronch CD Notice Period, AstraZeneca and its Affiliates shall not negotiate with or grant any rights to develop or commercialize the Bronch CD to any Third Party.&#160; If Insmed elects to enter into exclusive negotiations during the Bronch CD Notice Period, AstraZeneca shall negotiate exclusively and in good faith with Insmed for a period commencing upon the date AstraZeneca receives notice of such election from Insmed and expiring [***] thereafter (the &#147;
<B>
	Bronch CD Negotiation Period
</B>
	&#148;) with respect to commercially reasonable terms for the acquisition by Insmed, by license or otherwise, of the right to develop or commercialize the Bronch CD.&#160; Notwithstanding the foregoing in this Section&nbsp;2.7.2, each Party shall retain all discretion to determine, among other things, whether any proposed terms for Insmed&#146;s right to develop or commercialize any Bronch CD during the Bronch CD Negotiation Period are acceptable to such Party, and no Party shall be deemed to have acted without good faith solely because such Party does not agree to some or all of the other Party&#146;s proposed terms, or if the Parties cannot come to an agreement on mutually acceptable terms within the Bronch CD Negotiation Period.

<BR>
	ASTRAZENECA SUPPLY AND MANUFACTURING KNOW-HOW TRANSFER
<BR>
	ACTIVITIES

<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	3.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Supply of Licensed Products.
</B>
	&#160; No later than [***] after the Effective Date, or except as otherwise mutually agreed by the Parties, the Parties shall enter into a supply agreement pursuant to which AstraZeneca shall supply to Insmed specified quantities and dosage strengths of the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products to be used by Insmed for the conduct of the initial Phase&nbsp;2 Clinical Trial under the Development Plan (the &#147;
<B>
	Supply Agreement
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; The Parties agree that, except as may otherwise be mutually agreed, the Supply Agreement shall comply in all material respects with the draft terms set forth in
<U>
	Schedule 3.1
</U>
	hereof, which provide, without limitation, that Insmed shall pay [***] to Manufacture such Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in accordance with the payment terms and procedures to be set forth in the Supply Agreement.&#160; Such Supply Agreement shall be negotiated and agreed by the Parties in good faith.&#160; No later than the earlier of [***] after the Effective Date and first scheduled delivery by AstraZeneca to Insmed of Licensed Product pursuant to the Supply Agreement, AstraZeneca and Insmed shall enter into a reasonable and customary quality assurance agreement (the &#147;
<B>
	Quality Agreement
</B>
	&#148;) that shall set forth the terms and conditions upon which each Party will conduct its respective quality activities in connection with the Supply Agreement.&#160; Such Quality Agreement shall be negotiated and agreed by the Parties in good faith.&#160; Each Party shall duly and punctually perform all of its obligations under the Supply Agreement and the Quality Agreement.&#160; AstraZeneca shall Manufacture (or have Manufactured) all such Licensed Compound and Licensed Product in accordance with Applicable Law.&#160; Except as otherwise set forth in this Section&nbsp;3.1,&nbsp;Insmed shall have the sole right, at its expense, to Manufacture (or have Manufactured) and supply the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products for Exploitation in or for the Territory by Insmed and its Affiliates and its or their Sublicensees.

<U>
	Schedule&nbsp;1.12
</U>
	, including, for clarity, the

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	then-current process for the Manufacture of the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products, as well as any improvements or enhancements to such processes (the &#147;Manufacturing Process&#148;) and (ii)&nbsp;assist Insmed or its designee to contact any of AstraZeneca&#146;s Third Party manufacturers for purposes of Insmed or its designee entering into agreements for Manufacture of the Licensed Compound and the Licensed Products.&#160; AstraZeneca also shall, when and as reasonably requested by Insmed, respond to requests for additional information as may be necessary to Insmed or its designee to understand the Manufacturing Process.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	3.3.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Subsequent Manufacturing Know-How Transfer.
</B>
	&#160; Without limiting the foregoing in Section&nbsp;3.2, in the event that AstraZeneca or any of its Affiliates makes any invention, discovery or Improvement relating to, or that is otherwise necessary for, the Manufacture of the Licensed Compound or a Licensed Product during the Term, AstraZeneca shall promptly disclose such invention, discovery or Improvement to Insmed and shall, at Insmed&#146;s request, respond to requests for additional information with respect to such invention, discovery or Improvement as may be necessary to Insmed or its designee to understand the invention, discovery or Improvement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;4
<BR>
</FONT>
</B>
<B>
	DEVELOPMENT, REGULATORY AND COMMERCIALIZATION ACTIVITIES
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Development.
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.1.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Diligence.
</B>
	&#160; After the Effective Date, subject to AstraZeneca&#146;s specifically designated Manufacturing activities expressly set forth in Article&nbsp;3 and the Supply Agreement and the Quality Agreement, as between the Parties,&nbsp;Insmed shall be solely responsible for all aspects of the Development of the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in the Field in the Territory.&#160; Insmed shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to Develop, and obtain and maintain Regulatory Approvals for [***] in the Field in each of the Major Markets.&#160; Insmed shall perform or cause to be performed its Development activities hereunder in good scientific manner and in compliance with all Applicable Law.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.1.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Development Plan.
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.2IN;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	Attached hereto as
<U>
	Schedule&nbsp;4.1.2
</U>
	is the initial plan for the Development of the initial Licensed Product in the Field in the Major Markets (the &#147;
<B>
	Development Plan
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; Insmed shall review and revise the Development Plan periodically (at least annually) for the purpose of considering appropriate amendments thereto.&#160; In addition,&nbsp;Insmed may amend any Development Plan at any time.&#160; Upon the earlier of the end of the Royalty Term for each Licensed Product in each Major Market the obligation to maintain Development Plans shall be terminated.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

	Development Records.
</B>
	&#160; Insmed shall, and shall cause its Affiliates and its and their Sublicensees to, maintain, in good scientific manner, complete and accurate books and records pertaining to Development of Licensed Products hereunder, in sufficient detail to verify compliance with its obligations under this Agreement.&#160; Such books and records shall be kept in accordance with Insmed&#146;s customary business practices and be in compliance with Applicable Law and shall&nbsp;be retained by Insmed for at least [***] after the expiration or termination of this Agreement in its entirety or for such longer period as may be required by Applicable Law.&#160; AstraZeneca shall have the right, on a [***] basis, during normal business hours and upon reasonable advance notice to Insmed, to inspect and copy all such books and records maintained pursuant to this Section&nbsp;4.1.4;
<I>
	provided
</I>
	that AstraZeneca shall maintain such records and information disclosed therein in confidence in accordance with Article&nbsp;9.

	4.1.5.
</FONT>
</B>

	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Development Reports.
</B>
	&#160; Without limiting Section&nbsp;4.1.4, within [***] following [***] during which Insmed is conducting Development activities hereunder,&nbsp;Insmed shall provide AstraZeneca with written reports summarizing all material (i)&nbsp;Development activities it has performed, or caused to be performed, since the preceding report, (ii)&nbsp;Development activities in process and (iii)&nbsp;future activities it expects to initiate during the following [***] period.&#160; Each such report shall contain sufficient detail to enable AstraZeneca to assess Insmed&#146;s compliance with its obligations set forth in Sections&nbsp;4.1.1 and 4.1.2(ii), including Insmed&#146;s, or its Affiliates&#146; or its or their Sublicensees&#146; activities with respect to achieving Regulatory Approvals of Licensed Products in the Territory and clinical study results and results of other Development activities.&#160; Insmed also shall, when and as reasonably requested by AstraZeneca, respond to requests for additional information as may be necessary to AstraZeneca to understand Insmed&#146;s Development activities hereunder.

</U>
	&nbsp;to Insmed (the &#147;

	4.2.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;

<B>
	Communications and Filings with Regulatory Authorities.
</B>
	&#160; With respect to each Licensed Product,&nbsp;Insmed shall promptly provide AstraZeneca with:&#160; (i)&nbsp;copies of all pre-clinical and clinical data compiled in support of regulatory filings; (ii)&nbsp;copies of all regulatory correspondence to or from the Regulatory Authorities; (iii)&nbsp;final draft copies of material, non-recurring submissions and filings reasonably in advance of submission or filing (
<I>
	e.g.
</I>
	,&nbsp;INDs, CTAs, Drug Approval Applications, major supplements or amendments to the foregoing, material labeling supplements, Regulatory Authority meeting requests and core data sheets and filings related to new Indications and proposed labeling) to the Regulatory Authorities; (iv)&nbsp;notices of any revocations of Regulatory Approvals with respect to any such Licensed Product and any Licensed Product recalls or withdrawals in the Territory; and (v)&nbsp;reasonable responses to inquiries by AstraZeneca regarding the Regulatory Approval and Commercialization processes for any Licensed Product, including reasonable access to Insmed&#146;s personnel in connection with such inquiries.&#160; Insmed shall promptly provide AstraZeneca with copies of all other documents and correspondence pertaining to each Licensed Product after they have been submitted to, or received from, the Regulatory Authorities.&#160; Insmed shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to implement procedures reasonably designed to avoid any failure to provide any material required to be provided to AstraZeneca under this Section&nbsp;4.2.2 and to cure any such failure promptly after its discovery.
</P>

</FONT>
<B>
	Recalls, Suspensions or Withdrawals.
</B>
	&#160; Insmed shall notify AstraZeneca promptly (but in no event later than [***]) following its determination that any event, incident or circumstance has occurred that is reasonably likely to result in the need for a recall, market suspension or market withdrawal of a Licensed Product in the Field in the Territory and shall include in such notice the reasoning behind such determination and any supporting facts.&#160; As between the Parties,&nbsp;Insmed shall have the right to make the final determination whether to voluntarily implement any such recall, market suspension or market

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	withdrawal in the Field in the Territory;
<I>
	provided
</I>
	that prior to any implementation of such a recall, market suspension or market withdrawal,&nbsp;Insmed shall consult with AstraZeneca and shall consider AstraZeneca&#146;s comments in good faith.&#160; If a recall, market suspension or market withdrawal is mandated by a Regulatory Authority in the Territory, as between the Parties,&nbsp;Insmed shall initiate such a recall, market suspension or market withdrawal in compliance with Applicable Law.&#160; For all recalls, market suspensions or market withdrawals undertaken pursuant to this Section&nbsp;4.2.3, as between the Parties,&nbsp;Insmed shall be solely responsible for the execution thereof.&#160; Subject to Article&nbsp;11,&nbsp;Insmed shall be responsible for all costs of any such recall, market suspension or market withdrawal.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.2.4.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Global Safety Database.
</B>
	&#160; Insmed shall establish, hold and maintain (at Insmed&#146;s sole cost and expense) the global safety database for Licensed Products.&#160; AstraZeneca shall provide Insmed with information in the possession and Control of AstraZeneca as necessary for Insmed to comply with its pharmacovigilance responsibilities in the Territory, including, as applicable, any adverse drug experiences (including those events or experiences that are required to be reported to the FDA under 21 C.F.R. sections 312.32 or 314.80 or to foreign Regulatory Authorities under corresponding Applicable Law outside the United States), from pre-clinical or clinical laboratory, animal toxicology and pharmacology studies, clinical studies and commercial experiences with a Licensed Product, in each case, in the form reasonably requested by Insmed and an agreed upon timeframe.&#160; Each Party will provide the other Party with needed information for any aggregate reporting requirements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.3.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Commercialization.
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.3.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Diligence.
</B>
	&#160; As between the Parties,&nbsp;Insmed shall be solely responsible for Commercialization of the Licensed Products in the Field throughout the Territory at Insmed&#146;s own cost and expense.&#160; Without limitation of Section&nbsp;4.3.2,&nbsp;Insmed shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to Commercialize [***] in the Field in each of the Major Markets.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.3.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Commercialization Costs; Booking of Sales; Distribution.
</B>
	&#160; Insmed shall be responsible for all of its costs and expenses in connection with the Commercialization of the Licensed Products in the Field in the Territory.&#160; Insmed shall invoice and book sales, establish all terms of sale (including pricing and discounts) and warehouse and distribute the Licensed Products in the Field in the Territory and perform or cause to be performed all related services.&#160; Subject to Section&nbsp;4.2.3,&nbsp;Insmed shall handle all returns, recalls or withdrawals, order processing, invoicing, collection, distribution and inventory management with respect to the Licensed Products in the Territory.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	4.3.3.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Commercialization Records.
</B>
	&#160; Without limitation of Section&nbsp;7.10,&nbsp;Insmed shall maintain complete and accurate books and records pertaining to Commercialization of Licensed Products hereunder in sufficient detail to verify compliance with its obligations under this Agreement, and which shall be in compliance with Applicable Law and properly
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

	&#160; Insmed shall, and shall cause its Affiliates to, comply with all Applicable Law with respect to the Exploitation of Licensed Products.&#160; Insmed shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to avoid, and shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to cause its Affiliates and its and their Sublicensees, Third Party Distributors, employees, representatives, and agents to avoid, taking or failing to take any actions that Insmed knows or reasonably should know would jeopardize the goodwill or reputation of AstraZeneca or the Licensed Products or any Trademark associated therewith.&#160; Without limitation to the foregoing in this Section&nbsp;4.4,&nbsp;Insmed shall in all material respects conform its practices and procedures relating to the Commercialization of the Licensed Products and educating the medical community in the Territory with respect to the Licensed Products to any applicable industry association regulations, policies and guidelines, as the same may be amended from time to time, and Applicable Law.&#160; AstraZeneca shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to avoid, and shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to cause its Affiliates and its and their employees, representatives and agents to avoid, taking or failing to take any actions that AstraZeneca knows or reasonably should know would jeopardize the goodwill or reputation of Insmed or the Licensed Products or any Trademark associated therewith.

<BR>
</FONT>
</B>
<B>
	ASTRAZENECA&#146;S GRANT BACK RIGHTS

</B>
	&#160; During the period from the Effective Date until the [***] anniversary of the Effective Date (the &#147;
<B>

</B>
	&#148;), AstraZeneca shall have an exclusive option exercisable by written notice to Insmed to Develop the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in the Indications of COPD or Asthma up to and including Phase 2b Clinical Trials (the &#147;
<B>

</B>
	&#148;).

	Subject to AstraZeneca timely exercising the First Option in accordance with Section&nbsp;5.1,&nbsp;Insmed hereby grants to AstraZeneca:

	&nbsp;

<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	5.1.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	In accordance with Section&nbsp;6.2, upon AstraZeneca&#146;s exercise of the First Option, the Parties shall establish a Joint Steering Committee for purposes of coordination and information exchange to facilitate the Parties&#146; respective Development and Commercialization efforts involving the Licensed Compound and the Licensed Products, including reasonable exchange of clinical data, safety data and other data needed for Regulatory Documentation.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	5.1.3.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If AstraZeneca exercises the First Option, subject to any of Insmed&#146;s Manufacturing obligations that may be agreed between the Parties, as between the Parties, AstraZeneca shall be solely responsible for all aspects of the Development up to and including Phase 2b Clinical Trials of the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in the Indications of COPD or Asthma in the Territory.&#160; If AstraZeneca exercises the First Option, AstraZeneca shall use Commercially Reasonable Efforts to Develop at least one Licensed Product in at least one Indication of COPD or Asthma through a Phase 2 Clinical Trial.&#160; AstraZeneca shall perform or cause to be performed its Development activities hereunder in good scientific manner and in compliance with all Applicable Law.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	5.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Second Option.
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	5.2.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If AstraZeneca exercises the First Option prior to the expiration of the First Option Period and Develops the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in the Indications of COPD or Asthma, then, during the period from the exercise of the First Option until the earlier of (i)&nbsp;the [***] anniversary of AstraZeneca&#146;s issuance of the final study report for the first (1
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6.5PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;TOP:-3.0PT;">
	st
</FONT>
	) Phase 2b Clinical Study in the Indications of COPD or Asthma or (ii)&nbsp;the [***] anniversary of the exercise date of the First Option (the &#147;
<B>
	Second Option Period
</B>
	&#148;), AstraZeneca shall have an exclusive option exercisable by written notice to Insmed for an exclusive license under the AstraZeneca Patents, the AstraZeneca Know-How, the Joint Patents, the Joint Know-How, the Insmed Patents, the Insmed Know-How, the Assigned Regulatory Documentation, the AstraZeneca Regulatory Documentation and the Insmed Regulatory Documentation to the extent necessary or reasonably useful to enable AstraZeneca (x)&nbsp;to Develop the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in the Indications of COPD or Asthma, including activities beyond Phase 2b Clinical Trials, in the Territory, and (y)&nbsp;to Commercialize the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in the Indications of COPD and Asthma in the Territory (the &#147;
<B>
	Second Option
</B>
	&#148;).&#160; For the avoidance of doubt, this Section&nbsp;5.2.1 does not obligate AstraZeneca to initiate or complete any Phase 2b Clinical Trials for the Licensed Compound or the Licensed Products prior to exercise of the Second Option.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">

</FONT>

<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	If AstraZeneca exercises the Second Option prior to the expiration of the Second Option Period,&nbsp;Insmed and AstraZeneca shall negotiate in good faith commercially reasonable terms, including financial terms, for AstraZeneca&#146;s further Development and Commercialization of the License Compound and Licensed Products in the Indications of COPD and Asthma.&#160; Such agreement would include (i)&nbsp;diligence obligations for AstraZeneca to use

	&#160; For the sake of clarity,&nbsp;Insmed shall have no rights to Develop or Commercialize the Licensed Compound or Licensed Products in the Indications of COPD or Asthma unless:

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;6
<BR>
</FONT>
</B>
<B>
	ALLIANCE MANAGERS; JOINT STEERING COMMITTEE
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Alliance Managers.
</B>
	&#160; As of the Effective Date, each Party shall appoint a person who shall oversee contact between the Parties for all matters and shall have such other responsibilities as the Parties may agree in writing after the Effective Date (&#147;
<B>
	Alliance Manager
</B>
	&#148;), which person may be replaced at any time by notice in writing to the other Party.&#160; [***] shall be the initial Alliance Manager on behalf of AstraZeneca.&#160; [***] shall be the initial Alliance Manager on behalf of Insmed.&#160; The Alliance Managers shall work together to manage and facilitate the communication between the Parties under this Agreement, including the resolution (in accordance with the terms of this Agreement) of issues between the Parties that arise in connection with this Agreement.&#160; The Alliance Managers shall not have final decision-making authority with respect to any matter under this Agreement.&#160; In the event the Parties establish a Joint Steering Committee pursuant to Section&nbsp;6.2, the Alliance Managers shall oversee contact between the Parties for all matters between meetings of the JSC.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Joint Steering Committee.
</B>
	&#160; In the event AstraZeneca shall undertake any Development or Commercialization of Licensed Products pursuant to exercise of its option rights under Article&nbsp;5 or pursuant to an agreement entered into by the Parties under Section&nbsp;2.5, then the Parties promptly shall establish a joint steering committee (the &#147;
<B>
	Joint Steering Committee
</B>
	&#148; or &#147;
<B>
	JSC
</B>
	&#148;), which shall consist of representatives from each of the Parties, each with the requisite experience and seniority to enable such person to make decisions on behalf of the Parties with respect to the issues falling within the jurisdiction of the JSC.&#160; From time to time, each Party may substitute one or more of its representatives to the JSC on written notice to the other Party.&#160; Insmed shall select from its representatives the chairperson for the JSC, which chairperson may be changed from time to time, on written notice to AstraZeneca.&#160; The JSC shall:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.2.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
	serve as a forum for discussing and supervising Development of the Licensed Compound and Licensed Products in the Field in the Territory, including by overseeing the conduct of the Development activities and reviewing Development Plans and Development reports as provided in Section&nbsp;4.1.5, and by coordinating the reasonable exchange of clinical data, safety data and other data needed by each Party for its Regulatory Documentation;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.3.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Meetings and Minutes.
</B>
	&#160; The JSC shall meet as reasonably necessary to advance the Development of Licensed Products as mutually agreed by Parties&#146; respective representatives to the JSC.&#160; The location of such meetings shall alternate between locations designated by Insmed and locations designated by AstraZeneca.&#160; The chairperson of the JSC shall be responsible for calling meetings on no less than [***] notice, unless exigent circumstances require shorter notice.&#160; Each Party shall make all proposals for agenda items at least [***] in advance of the applicable meeting and shall provide all appropriate information with respect to such proposed items at least [***] in advance of the applicable meeting;
<I>
	provided
</I>
	that under exigent circumstances requiring input by the JSC, a Party may provide its agenda items to the other Party within a shorter period of time in advance of the meeting or may propose that there not be a specific agenda for a particular meeting, so long as the other Party consents to such later addition of such agenda items or the absence of a specific agenda for such meeting.&#160; The chairperson of the JSC shall prepare and circulate for review and approval of the Parties minutes of each meeting within [***] after the meeting.&#160; The Parties shall agree on the minutes of each meeting promptly, but in no event later than the next meeting of the JSC.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.3.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Procedural Rules.
</B>
	&#160; The JSC shall have the right to adopt such standing rules&nbsp;as shall be necessary for its work, to the extent that such rules&nbsp;are not inconsistent with this Agreement.&#160; A quorum of the JSC shall exist whenever there is present at a meeting at least one (1)&nbsp;representative appointed by each Party.&#160; Representatives of the Parties on the JSC may attend a meeting either in person or by telephone, video conference or similar means in which each participant can hear what is said by, and be heard by, the other participants.&#160; Representation by proxy shall be allowed.&#160; Subject to Section&nbsp;6.3.3, the JSC shall take action by consensus of the representatives present at a meeting at which a quorum exists, with each Party having a single vote irrespective of the number of representatives of such Party in attendance or by a written resolution signed by at least one (1)&nbsp;representative appointed by each Party.&#160; Employees or consultants of a Party who are not representatives of the Parties on the JSC may attend meetings of the JSC;
<I>
	provided, however
</I>
	, that such attendees (i)&nbsp;shall not vote or otherwise participate in the decision-making process of the JSC and (ii)&nbsp;are bound by obligations of confidentiality and non-disclosure at least as protective of the other Party as those set forth in Article&nbsp;9.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="1" WIDTH="25%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:BLACK;">
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	*** Certain information on this page&nbsp;has been omitted and filed separately with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Confidential treatment has been requested with respect to the omitted portions.
</FONT>
</P>

<A NAME="eolPage38"></A>
<BR CLEAR="ALL" STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS;">
<DIV STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.3.3.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Decision-Making.
</B>
	&#160; Except for matters outside the jurisdiction and authority of the JSC (including as set forth in Section&nbsp;6.3.4), if the JSC cannot, or does not, reach consensus on an issue, then such issue shall be resolved pursuant to Section&nbsp;13.5.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.3.4.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Limitations on Authority.
</B>
	&#160; Without limitation to the foregoing, the Parties hereby agree that matters explicitly reserved to the consent, approval or other decision-making authority of one or both Parties, as expressly provided in this Agreement, are outside the jurisdiction and authority of the JSC, including (i)&nbsp;amendment, modification or waiver of compliance with this Agreement (which may only be amended or modified as provided in Section&nbsp;13.8 or compliance with which may only be waived as provided in Section&nbsp;13.11), and (ii)&nbsp;such other matters as are reserved to the consent, approval, agreement or other decision-making authority of either or both Parties in this Agreement that are not required by this Agreement to be considered by the JSC prior to the exercise of such consent, approval or other decision-making authority.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	6.3.5.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Discontinuation; Disbandment; Annual Reports
</B>
	.&#160; The JSC shall continue to exist until the first to occur of: (i)&nbsp;the Parties mutually agreeing to disband the JSC; and (ii)&nbsp;AstraZeneca discontinuing any Development or Commercialization activities with respect to Licensed Products, at which time AstraZeneca shall provide to Insmed written notice of its intention to disband the JSC.&#160; Upon the occurrence of either of the foregoing, (x)&nbsp;the JSC shall disband, have no further responsibilities or authority under this Agreement and will be considered dissolved by the Parties and (y)&nbsp;any requirement of a Party to provide Information or other materials to the JSC shall be deemed a requirement to provide such Information or other materials to the other Party and after consultation with AstraZeneca and taking AstraZeneca&#146;s comments, if any, into consideration in good faith,&nbsp;Insmed shall have the right to decide all matters that are subject to the review or approval by the JSC hereunder, with any Disputes to be resolved pursuant to Section&nbsp;13.5.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ARTICLE&nbsp;7
<BR>
	PAYMENTS AND RECORDS
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

	7.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Upfront Payment.
</B>
	&#160; In partial consideration of the rights granted by AstraZeneca to Insmed hereunder, no later than thirty (30) days following the Effective Date,&nbsp;Insmed shall pay AstraZeneca a nonrefundable and noncreditable upfront amount equal to thirty million Dollars ($30,000,000).
</P>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

	&#160; Insmed acknowledges that (i)&nbsp;the AstraZeneca Know-How and the Information included in the AstraZeneca Regulatory Documentation licensed to Insmed is proprietary and valuable and that, without the AstraZeneca Know-How and such Information,&nbsp;Insmed would not be able to obtain and maintain Regulatory Approvals with respect to the Licensed Products, (ii)&nbsp;access to the AstraZeneca Know-How and the rights with respect to the AstraZeneca Regulatory Documentation has provided Insmed with a competitive advantage in the marketplace beyond the exclusivity afforded by the AstraZeneca Patents and the regulatory exclusivity and (iii)&nbsp;the milestone payments and royalties set forth in Sections&nbsp;7.2.1 and 7.2.2 and Section&nbsp;7.3.1, respectively, are, in part, intended to compensate AstraZeneca for such exclusivity and such competitive advantage.&#160; The Parties agree that the royalty rates set forth in Section&nbsp;7.3.1 reflect an efficient and reasonable blended allocation of the value provided by AstraZeneca to Insmed.

	&#160; Insmed shall have no obligation to pay any royalty with respect to Net Sales of any Licensed Product in any country after the Royalty Term for such Licensed Product in such country has expired.&#160; Upon expiration of the Royalty Term with respect to a Licensed Product in any country, the license grants to Insmed in Section&nbsp;2.1, as applicable, with respect to such Licensed Product shall become non-exclusive, fully-paid, royalty-free, perpetual and irrevocable for such Licensed Product in such country, subject to any agreement entered into between the Parties pursuant to Section&nbsp;2.5 or Section&nbsp;5.2.

	in any country in the Territory during the Royalty Term for a Licensed Product, one or more Generic Products are sold by any Person other than Insmed, its Affiliates, or its or their Sublicensees, and such Generic Products have sales in such country resulting in a reduction of the number of unit sales of the corresponding Licensed Product in

	pursuant to Section&nbsp;8.6,&nbsp;Insmed enters into an agreement with a Third Party in order to obtain a license to a Patent Right or other intellectual property right that relates to the Licensed Compound, a Licensed Product or any AstraZeneca Patent or AstraZeneca Know-How and is reasonably necessary to Exploit the Licensed Compound in the Field in a country in the Territory or otherwise use AstraZeneca Patents or AstraZeneca Know-How in such country,&nbsp;Insmed shall be entitled to deduct from milestone payments and royalties payable hereunder in a given Calendar Year with respect to such Licensed Product in such country [***] percent ([***]%) of any fees, milestone payments or royalties paid to such Third Party in such Calendar Year under such agreement, solely to the extent that such fees, milestone payments or royalties paid to such Third Party are triggered by activities involving a Licensed Product that would, absent such agreement, infringe a Patent Right or otherwise misappropriate an intellectual property right of such Third Party that is licensed under such agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

</B>
	&#160; In no event shall the amounts payable to AstraZeneca under Sections&nbsp;7.2 and 7.3 be reduced by operation of Section&nbsp;7.4 by more than [***] percent ([***]%) of what would otherwise be due by operation of Sections&nbsp;7.2 and 7.3 without regard to Section&nbsp;7.4 in any Calendar Year as a result of the reductions set forth in Section&nbsp;7.4.&#160; Any unused reduction may be carried over into subsequent Calendar Years.&#160; For clarity, to the extent the adjustments in Section&nbsp;7.4 or this Section&nbsp;7.5 cover periods in which payments are due based on more than one royalty rate described in Section&nbsp;7.3.1, the Net Sales to which such adjustments apply shall be distributed on a pro rata basis among the applicable royalty rates set forth in Section&nbsp;7.3.1.

	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>

	Royalty Payments and Reports.
</B>
	&#160; Insmed shall calculate all amounts payable to AstraZeneca pursuant to Section&nbsp;7.3.1 at the end of each Calendar Quarter, which amounts shall be converted to Dollars, in accordance with Section&nbsp;7.7.&#160; Insmed shall pay to AstraZeneca the royalty amounts due with respect to a given Calendar Quarter within [***] after the end of such Calendar Quarter.&#160; Each payment of royalties due to AstraZeneca shall be accompanied by a statement specifying, on a Licensed Product-by-Licensed Product basis, the amount of Invoiced Sales, Net Sales and deductions taken to arrive at Net Sales attributable to each Licensed Product in each country the Territory during the applicable Calendar Quarter (including such amounts expressed in local currency and as converted to Dollars) and a calculation of the amount of royalty payment due on such Net Sales for such Calendar Quarter.&#160; Without limiting the generality of the foregoing,&nbsp;Insmed shall require its Affiliates and Sublicensees to account for their Net Sales and to provide

	Mode of Payment; Offsets.&#160;
</B>
	All payments to AstraZeneca under this Agreement shall be made by deposit of Dollars in the requisite amount to such bank account as AstraZeneca may from time to time designate by notice to Insmed.&#160; For the purpose of calculating any sums due under, or otherwise reimbursable pursuant to, this Agreement (including the calculation of Net Sales expressed in currencies other than Dollars),&nbsp;Insmed shall convert any amount expressed in a foreign currency into Dollar equivalents using its, its Affiliates&#146; or Sublicensees&#146;, as applicable, standard conversion methodology consistent with GAAP.&#160; Insmed shall have no right to offset, set off or deduct any amounts from or against the amounts due to AstraZeneca hereunder.

	7.8.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	General.
</B>
	&#160; The milestone payments and royalties payable by Insmed to AstraZeneca pursuant to this Agreement (each, a &#147;
<B>
	Payment
</B>
	&#148;) shall be paid free and clear of any and all taxes, except for any withholding taxes required by Applicable Law.&#160; Except as provided in this Section&nbsp;7.8, AstraZeneca shall be solely responsible for paying any and all taxes (other than withholding taxes required by Applicable Law to be deducted from Payments and remitted by Insmed) levied on account of, or measured in whole or in part by reference to, any Payments it receives.&#160; Insmed shall deduct or withhold from the Payments any taxes that it is required by Applicable Law to deduct or withhold.&#160; Notwithstanding the foregoing, if AstraZeneca is entitled under any applicable tax treaty to a reduction of rate of, or the elimination of, applicable withholding tax, it may deliver to Insmed or the appropriate governmental authority (with the assistance of Insmed to the extent that this is reasonably required and is requested in writing) the prescribed forms necessary to reduce the applicable rate of withholding or to relieve Insmed of its obligation to withhold such tax and Insmed shall apply the reduced rate of withholding or dispense with withholding, as the case may be;
<I>
	provided
</I>
	that Insmed has received evidence of AstraZeneca&#146;s delivery of all applicable forms (and, if necessary, its receipt of appropriate governmental authorization) at least [***] prior to the time that the Payments are due.&#160; If, in accordance with the foregoing,&nbsp;Insmed withholds any amount, it shall pay to AstraZeneca the balance when due, make timely payment to the proper taxing authority of the withheld amount and send to AstraZeneca proof of such payment within [***] following such payment.&#160; In case of an assignment of this Agreement in accordance with Section&nbsp;13.3, and if an assignee under Applicable Law is required to deduct or withhold any taxes from any amount payable under or in respect of this Agreement, and the amount so deducted or withheld exceeds the amount that would have been deducted or withheld absent an assignment, the assignee shall increase the amount payable so as to ensure that, after such deduction or withholding (together with any increased deduction or withholding required as a result of the increase in the amount payable), the payee receives and retains the amount that it would have received and retained in the absence of an assignment (together with any increased deduction or withholding required as a result of the increase in the amount payable).

</B>
	&#148;).&#160; The decision of the Auditor shall be final and the costs of such arbitration as well as the initial audit shall be borne between the Parties in such manner as the Auditor shall determine.&#160; Not later than [***] after such decision and in accordance with such decision, (i)&nbsp;Insmed shall pay the additional amounts, with interest from the date originally due as provided in Section&nbsp;7.9, (ii)&nbsp;AstraZeneca shall reimburse the excess payments, as applicable.

<B>

	ARTICLE&nbsp;8
<BR>
	INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
</FONT>
</B>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.0IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	8.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Ownership of Intellectual Property.
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	8.1.1.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Ownership of Technology.
</B>
	&#160; Subject to Section&nbsp;8.1.2, as between the Parties, each Party shall own and retain all right, title and interest in and to any and all: (i)&nbsp;Information,&nbsp;Improvements and other inventions that are conceived, discovered, developed or otherwise made by or on behalf of such Party or its Affiliates or its or their (sub)licensees (or Sublicensees), as applicable, under or in connection with this Agreement, whether or not patented or patentable and any and all Patents and other intellectual property rights with respect thereto, except to the extent that any such Information or invention or any Patent or intellectual property rights with respect thereto, is Joint Know-How or Joint Patents; and (ii)&nbsp;other Information, inventions, Patents and other intellectual property rights that are owned or otherwise controlled (other than pursuant to the license grants set forth in Sections&nbsp;2.1 and 2.2) by such Party or its Affiliates or its or their (sub)licensees (or Sublicensees) (as applicable) outside of this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:1.5IN;">
<B>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	8.1.2.
</FONT>
</B>
<FONT SIZE="1" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:3.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<B>
	Ownership of Joint Patents and Joint Know-How.
</B>
	&#160; As between the Parties, each of AstraZeneca and Insmed shall own an equal, undivided interest in any and all:&#160; (i)&nbsp;Information,&nbsp;Improvements and other inventions that are conceived, discovered, developed or otherwise made jointly by or on behalf of AstraZeneca or its Affiliates or its or their (sub)licensees, on the one hand, and Insmed or its Affiliates or its or their Sublicensees, on the other hand, in connection with the work conducted under or in connection with this Agreement, whether or not patented or patentable (the &#147;
<B>
	Joint Know-How
</B>
	&#148;); and (ii)&nbsp;Patents (the &#147;
<B>
	Joint Patents
</B>
	&#148;) and other intellectual property rights with respect to the Information,
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN:0IN 0IN .0001PT;">
<HR SIZE="1" WIDTH="25%" NOSHADE ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="COLOR:BLACK;">
</DIV>

	*** Certain information on this page&nbsp;has been omitted and filed separately with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Confidential treatment has been requested with respect to the omitted portions.
